Description: Handle sliver of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp with star symbols. Clay fine light brown; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.181, 21). Name Sarapion. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0010.04.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0779)
